---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Callout from "../../components/Callout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Getting Started">
  <h1>Getting Started</h1>
  <p>This section covers the first 30 minutes after the site is deployed: signing in, exploring Site Settings, and publishing your first page.</p>
  <Callout type="info">Most of these tasks require Administrator privileges. Editors can do day-to-day content work; deployment and configuration are admin-only.</Callout>
  <h2>Walkthrough order</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><a href="/docs/getting-started/first-login">First login</a> — sign in with the seeded admin and change the password.</li>
    <li><a href="/docs/getting-started/site-settings">Site Settings tour</a> — what each tab controls.</li>
    <li><a href="/docs/getting-started/creating-your-first-content">Create your first content</a> — a page, a news item, a sermon.</li>
  </ol>
</BaseLayout>
